2f/1fb50/Walk-Ons-UTSA-Band-Performing-scaled-1.jpg 1001w,\n/static/dc57e769e17cde22628691764306f82f/94590/Walk-Ons-UTSA-Band-Performing-scaled-1.jpg 1334w,\n/static/dc57e769e17cde22628691764306f82f/bb9a8/Walk-Ons-UTSA-Band-Performing-scaled-1.jpg 2560w\" src=\"/static/dc57e769e17cde22628691764306f82f/56505/Walk-Ons-UTSA-Band-Performing-scaled-1.jpg\" alt=\"UTSA Marching Band Performs at Walk-Ons VIP Event\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></span><br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nThe PM Group celebrated with the community at the new <a href=\"https://www.walk-ons.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Walk-On&#8217;s Bistreaux &amp; Bar</a> VIP event earlier this month. The <a href=\"http://www.utsabands.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">UTSA Marching Band</a> played for the attendees and Ron Ellis, UTSA Marching Band Director, received a $4,000 donation for their participation. Their performance enhanced the game-day atmosphere that San Antonio’s newest sports bar provides.  Director of Athletics, Lynn Hickey, and UTSA Head Football Coach, Frank Wilson, also joined in the festivities.<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\n<span class=\" wp-image-2342 aligncenter inline-gatsby-image-wrapper gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%;width:796px\" data-reactroot=\"\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:37.688442211055275%\"></span><img aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:0;transition-delay:500ms\"/><picture><source srcSet=\"/static/2f18476e5397b707e392fbaee27a6035/5bedf/walk-ons-check.png 199w,\n/static/2f18476e5397b707e392fbaee27a6035/48cfd/walk-ons-check.png 398w,\n/static/2f18476e5397b707e392fbaee27a6035/06b13/walk-ons-check.png 796w,\n/static/2f18476e5397b707e392f